Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.01,0:00:14.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why is Lancer helping them?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.26,0:00:16.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.56,0:00:19.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.68,0:00:22.34,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No, it is a trivial matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.34,0:00:23.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Please do not trouble yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.44,0:00:26.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is nothing to be concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.40,0:00:30.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.57,0:00:32.42,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.07,0:00:35.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is something that I would like to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.71,0:00:36.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.66,0:00:40.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Earlier, in the chapel, you said something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.87,0:00:43.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That you would be unable to \Nfulfill your own objective.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.32,0:00:49.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But to my knowledge, you have \Nno desire of your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.77,0:00:53.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The desire to obtain something. \NTo destroy something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.10,0:00:55.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To forgive something.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.36,0:01:00.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have never spoken of any of these \Ndesires that all humans possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.39,0:01:04.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A man like you had an objective?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.65,0:01:08.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.86,0:01:11.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was treated as something not human.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.69,0:01:14.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I grew up never doubting that to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.53,0:01:17.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, I eventually took a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.09,0:01:21.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I bore that person no ill will,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.33,0:01:26.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and it was not a matter of me\Nstanding to profit from killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:31.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was mechanical, carried out \Nas per another's orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.51,0:01:36.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,At that moment, I pushed from my \Nmind the notion that I was human.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.51,0:01:40.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of any problems with the \Nenvironment in which I was raised,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.72,0:01:42.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,my choices were mine alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.86,0:01:46.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,As you said, I have no wish \Nto return to my former self.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.73,0:01:52.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I have always believed that I am solely \Nresponsible for the way I live.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.11,0:01:54.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.70,0:01:59.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I must return something, which must have \Nonce existed, to its rightful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.91,0:02:05.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all this time, having a goal beyond \Nsimple existence is strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.27,0:02:08.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a completely self-centered thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.88,0:02:12.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But in the end, that's what all wishes are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.41,0:03:51.27,Title,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(317,539)}#17  The Dark Sword Bares Its Fangs
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.43,0:03:49.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We need to defeat Caster before the fight
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.12,0:03:51.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,between Lancer and Archer ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.02,0:03:52.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.30,0:03:55.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure I can leave Caster to you, Tohsaka?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.27,0:03:57.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.00,0:04:01.17,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,She'll probably have me on the ropes the \Nwhole time, but stay out of it, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.82,0:04:05.95,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You just keep Kuzuki-sensei \Nas far away as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.49,0:04:07.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.33,0:04:10.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Berserker is gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.66,0:04:13.85,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The one who'll be the biggest problem is Blondie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.42,0:04:18.44,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if we can get Archer and Saber \Nback from Caster, we can beat him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.09,0:04:22.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And then the Holy Grail War will be over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:31.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like she wants to wrap this up, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:40.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I graciously spared your life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.24,0:04:43.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have you come to throw it away, little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.91,0:04:47.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come to throw something away, \Nbut to take back what's mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:51.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Beating you, someone I really \Ncan't stand, in the process.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.29,0:04:54.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.89,0:04:58.23,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I offer my compliments on winning \NLancer to your side.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.59,0:05:01.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you still have fewer pawns on the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.13,0:05:03.45,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you so transparently a child that
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.45,0:05:05.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,you cannot manage such simple arithmetic?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.10,0:05:09.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I've been thinking this for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.01,0:05:11.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That outfit of yours is a bit, you know...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.68,0:05:16.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A purple robe, in this day and age? \NWhat kind of bumpkin wears that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.73,0:05:19.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Also, this is your idea of a magic workshop?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.73,0:05:22.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're so stuck in the past, it's laughable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.56,0:05:24.32,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, dear.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.32,0:05:28.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are all mages of this era so foolhardy?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.08,0:05:33.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Now I understand why Archer deserted you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.12,0:05:36.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kuzuki can see everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.29,0:05:39.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That we're trying a divide-and-conquer strategy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.21,0:05:41.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,and that you have a trick up your sleeve.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.69,0:05:45.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And even knowing that, he's letting \NCaster do things her way.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.13,0:05:48.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we get started, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.35,0:05:50.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This will be my third time facing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.22,0:05:53.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired of looking at your ugly face.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.64,0:05:55.98,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I'll finish you off for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.98,0:05:57.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bold words.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:01.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do you honestly think you can \Ndefeat me, little girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.38,0:06:06.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I can beat your parlor tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.53,0:06:08.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Is there any doubt?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.07,0:06:13.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,A first-rate mage like myself could never \Nlose to a third-rate hack like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.70,0:06:18.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can see by your insolence that you \Nare in need of harsh discipline.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:20.25,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace on!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.63,0:06:27.56,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He knows exactly what our plan is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.56,0:06:30.01,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I won't be able to buy time for long.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.39,0:06:33.66,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,The Master, a close-quarters specialist, \Nwho had even Saber on the ropes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:36.02,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Martial arts and magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.02,0:06:39.34,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We have no chance of winning \Nwhen we're outclassed in both.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.48,0:06:44.63,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Meaning this fight will be to \Nsee how long we can hold out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.71,0:06:50.05,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,against superior opponents before \NTohsaka puts her plan into motion!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.39,0:07:17.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't like that other night, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:21.83,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry I had to go easy on you last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.83,0:07:24.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My stupid Master used a Command Seal
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.38,0:07:28.30,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,to order me to return alive, without killing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.61,0:07:34.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not bound by that order now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.41,0:07:36.06,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I won't hold back...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:43.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.47,0:07:57.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't figure you out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.68,0:08:03.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're this skilled, but you \Nchose to side with Caster?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.61,0:08:07.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Working with the little lady, you probably \Nwould have been a match for Caster.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.44,0:08:13.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting you to mouth off, \Nbut you're still going on about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.29,0:08:17.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I chose the option with the higher chance \Nof success, however slight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.44,0:08:18.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Was that why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.79,0:08:21.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It was stupid of me to even ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.18,0:08:22.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No argument there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:26.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But that isn't a certain path to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:34.36,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have a fatal lack of pride in your sword skills.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.39,0:08:36.47,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.91,0:08:39.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I am devoid of pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.32,0:08:42.39,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But why does that bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.39,0:08:44.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does it dishonor all heroes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.81,0:08:48.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make me laugh, Lancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.12,0:08:51.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Dishonor can be washed away with success.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.09,0:08:57.14,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Feed your leftover pride to that dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.16,0:09:03.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Did you just call her a dog, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.42,0:09:05.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's the truth, Cú Chulainn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.72,0:09:10.13,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you have a hero's pride, \Ncast it aside while you still can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.51,0:09:12.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Well said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.09,0:09:14.15,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then you first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.39,0:09:21.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard of my spear's special \Nability, haven't you, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.39,0:09:23.64,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:26.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It has a cunning curse that \Nreverses cause and effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.77,0:09:31.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It's certainly fearsome, but unless you get \Nclose, it's nothing but a sharp stinger.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.94,0:09:32.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,True.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.99,0:09:37.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But spears can also be used like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.99,0:09:40.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Here it comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.16,0:09:43.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Accept my blow as a gift for one about to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.34,0:09:53.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm well aware...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.38,0:09:58.22,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gae Bolg, the spear whose curse \Nkills with a single blow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.22,0:10:01.45,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I know that when thrown, it is an \Nanti-army Noble Phantasm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.43,0:10:04.93,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It strikes for the heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.93,0:10:06.50,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Careful aim is crucial.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.50,0:10:10.46,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, taking the blow \Nhead-on is the only way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.07,0:10:18.59,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Gae Bolg!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.91,0:10:28.77,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am the bone of my sword...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.40,0:10:33.73,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Rho Aias!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.31,0:10:44.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.82,0:10:55.50,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Not even Aias,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:11:00.03,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,which deflected the Trojan War's great \Nhero's throws, can take this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.39,0:11:29.12,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.81,0:11:33.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,To think there is a spear that \Ncan penetrate Rho Aias...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.48,0:11:37.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you have is mightier than \Neven the original Gungnir.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.70,0:11:40.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.88,0:11:43.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Just a simple bowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.16,0:11:44.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Bull.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.67,0:11:48.16,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Do bowmen have shields that can \Nwithstand a Noble Phantasm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.46,0:11:50.62,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Under the right circumstances, they might.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.62,0:11:53.04,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But you can see that it didn't entirely work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.04,0:11:55.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I expended most of my mana,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.67,0:12:00.05,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,one of my arms is useless, and my \NAias was completely destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.05,0:12:05.03,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it... That was the most \Npowerful defense I had.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.14,0:12:08.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But enough about that, Lancer. \NHave you noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.60,0:12:11.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster must be hard pressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.57,0:12:13.58,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Her prying eyes have stopped watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.82,0:12:17.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Have they now?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.28,0:12:21.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I thought that might be what you were up to...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.22,0:12:22.22,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You sly bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.70,0:12:24.59,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That was your intent all along?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.91,0:12:25.88,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.88,0:12:27.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.24,0:12:30.27,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I only use the means that give me \Nthe highest chance of victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.83,0:12:34.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I really hate your guts, you bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:37.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But my job is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.77,0:12:49.49,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sieben!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:57.71,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What was that tremor a minute ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.28,0:13:05.30,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,His goal is to take away my two swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.30,0:13:10.31,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't expect much integrity from rushed \Nprojections and impromptu swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.31,0:13:12.41,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can make two more at most.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.21,0:13:22.26,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My job is to keep Kuzuki occupied.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.26,0:13:26.20,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not going to quit before that job is finished...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.01,0:13:53.15,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Acht!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:13:59.63,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You struggle so valiantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.63,0:14:03.89,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I did not think that you had such a \Ntrick up your sleeve, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.05,0:14:08.82,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sieben!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.56,0:14:17.40,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You are fending off my attacks beautifully.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:19.19,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Valiant indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.19,0:14:23.75,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But surely you need not use the entire stone \Nif you are only protecting yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.28,0:14:27.49,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know that I'm using them wastefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.91,0:14:30.97,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster's spells cover too broad an area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.97,0:14:33.10,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Kuzuki is probably protected,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.88,0:14:37.94,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but if I don't nullify her spells, \NShirou will be burned to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.25,0:14:41.29,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still intend to stay on the defensive?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.29,0:14:44.76,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Your determination is impressive, \Nbut how long can you hold out?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.76,0:14:48.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If all you do is block me, \Nthe outcome is obvious, little girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.93,0:14:50.97,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Six gems left...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.10,0:14:53.87,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sechs, ein Fluß.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.87,0:14:55.04,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Ein Halt!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:00.73,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Fünf, drei, vier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.77,0:15:05.32,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Der Riese und brennt das ein Ende!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.62,0:15:20.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, have you finished?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.93,0:15:23.93,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have more gems, do you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.93,0:15:27.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why not keep trying until you run out?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:30.86,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Those were my biggest guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.86,0:15:32.60,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If those failed,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.60,0:15:36.95,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,then even if I combine a hundred gems, \Nmy magic won't be powerful enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.95,0:15:40.31,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I see that you finally understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.31,0:15:43.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That no matter what you try, \Nyou are no match for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.15,0:15:46.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But it was quite entertaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.67,0:15:50.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It has been some time since \NI last fought a magic duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.57,0:15:54.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I consider you worthwhile, if only for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.20,0:15:58.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Does that frustrate you? \NNevertheless, it is the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.87,0:16:00.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You should actually be proud.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.79,0:16:04.73,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You forced me into a magic duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.73,0:16:09.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is only a matter of time before\Nthat boy is beaten by my Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.84,0:16:16.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Let's wrap this up before then, shall we?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.81,0:16:23.21,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Stark, Groß zwei!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.20,0:16:42.81,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You profess to be a mage, \Nyet you fight with your fists?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.81,0:16:47.71,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but for mages nowadays, \Nthe art of self-defense
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.48,0:16:49.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,is a required subject!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:00.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.76,0:17:07.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.08,0:17:08.53,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Tohsaka!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.24,0:17:12.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You missed your chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.50,0:17:16.01,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Failing to kill her after four strikes \Nis a sign of your inexperience.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.70,0:17:19.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You have my thanks, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.70,0:17:23.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Had you not intervened, I would have been defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.33,0:17:24.52,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Spare me the flattery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.87,0:17:26.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,What you need to do now is wake up Saber.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.94,0:17:29.61,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Clearly, these are not opponents to be underestimated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.86,0:17:30.84,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.84,0:17:33.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is a wise decision, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.55,0:17:34.55,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.55,0:17:38.37,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If only you'd been a few seconds faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.31,0:17:40.37,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Trace...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.81,0:17:42.79,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.96,0:17:46.46,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Souichirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.67,0:18:15.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Are you unharmed, Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.08,0:18:15.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.55,0:18:18.35,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I am glad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.35,0:18:20.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It would not do...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:23.18,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,if you were to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.93,0:18:26.10,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,It is a pity, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.10,0:18:29.25,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I had finally found my wish.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.65,0:18:31.94,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need to grieve.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.94,0:18:35.78,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I will fulfill your wish in your place.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.86,0:18:40.26,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.98,0:18:43.72,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,After all, until this moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.04,0:18:52.67,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,my wish was already being granted...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:14.79,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.79,0:19:16.80,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'd always suspected,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.80,0:19:18.41,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,but is it true?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.36,0:19:20.95,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,"Trace on."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.95,0:19:23.41,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That's definitely what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.41,0:19:26.72,Default - italics,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,He spoke exactly the same words that I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.50,0:19:30.33,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,We had a traitor within our ranks, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.33,0:19:33.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This was your goal all along, wasn't it, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.82,0:19:34.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.92,0:19:38.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,But if I had to pick a metaphor, \Nthe Trojan Horse would be more apt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.97,0:19:42.99,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Since it was a Grecian hero who was just defeated.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.99,0:19:44.68,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:48.97,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster made a mistake when she \Nlet a man like you into her ranks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.52,0:19:55.50,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to continue, I won't stop you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.50,0:19:56.82,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.82,0:19:58.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you still going, Kuzuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.90,0:20:00.57,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.57,0:20:02.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't have any reason to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.51,0:20:05.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. I have no reason to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.66,0:20:10.87,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Like you, I never had any \Ninterest in the Holy Grail.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.87,0:20:11.60,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.24,0:20:16.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,This is something that I started.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.80,0:20:21.09,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I agreed to this, without caring \Nabout matters of good or evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.09,0:20:24.11,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I can't quit without seeing it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.13,0:21:04.24,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Saber...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.75,0:21:07.74,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.92,0:21:11.77,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Wha?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.08,0:21:15.00,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Damn, I missed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:17.08,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer! What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.57,0:21:19.69,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You can drop the act!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.69,0:21:21.28,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Caster's been beaten,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.28,0:21:23.38,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,so I won't stand for any more of your nonsense!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.86,0:21:25.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You won't stand for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.66,0:21:28.70,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I need your permission?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.70,0:21:31.02,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't my Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.71,0:21:36.48,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,My pact with you was severed.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.88,0:21:37.92,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.42,0:21:39.96,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you doing this, Archer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.96,0:21:42.90,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You still want to kill Shirou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.26,0:21:44.51,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.51,0:21:47.66,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,I'll kill Emiya Shirou with my own two hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.66,0:21:54.43,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,That is the only desire I, a man \Nreduced to a Guardian, have.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.15,0:23:28.86,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Leave this place, you and your false mentor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.86,0:23:31.07,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Archer, your wish is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.07,0:23:34.21,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,You want to give me a piece of \Nyour mind? Fine, let's hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.21,0:23:37.91,Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,Then I entrust my fate to your sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.18,0:23:39.93,Next,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(486,1)}Next Time \NA Destiny Forged in the Beginning
